title: ‘Bondi Terror’: The untold story of the massacre and the fight for a Royal Commission
description: Sky News host Sharri Markson and CEOs of the Executive Council of Australian Jury Alex Ryvchin announce their upcoming book "Bondi Terror" to be published by HarperCollins.   The book aims to preserve the stories of the Bondi massacre, the two-year anti-Semitism crisis leading up to it, and the aftermath, including the fight for a Royal Commission.   It will honour the victims, heroes, and the predominantly migrant community affected by the tragedy, educating future generations about the consequences of government inaction and the road to terror.

title: BREAKING: Shocking arrest of former prince Andrew
description: Reports have emerged the former Prince Andrew has been arrested by police at his home near the Sandringham Estate.   The BBC has reported eight officers arrived in six Metropolitan Police vehicles and have taken Andrew into custody.   The arrest is allegedly related to potential misconduct in public office during his time as a UK trade envoy, with suggestions that he may have improperly shared privileged information, potentially with Jeffrey Epstein.  While the details are still unfolding, this development marks a significant turn in the ongoing scrutiny surrounding Andrew's ties to Epstein and the accusations against him.

title: Former prince Andrew arrested in the UK over alleged misconduct in public office
description: Sky News host Paul Murray announces Thames Valley Police have arrested a man in his 60s, believed to be former prince Andrew, from Norfolk, on suspicion of misconduct in public office.  “There is a statement which we have just received here at Sky News on the other side of the world, and it comes from the Thames Valley Police,” Mr Murray said.  “We have today arrested a man in his 60’s from Norfolk on suspicion of misconduct in public office.  "We will not be naming the arrested man, as per national guidance.   “Assistant Chief Constable Oliver Wright said, following a thorough assessment, we have now opened an investigation into this allegation of misconduct in public office.  “Not a charge at this stage but an investigation.”

title: ‘Victim of his own success’: The Republican Party needs to stop relying on Trump
description: Former White House press secretary Sean Spicer warns the Republican Party must stop relying solely on US President Donald Trump’s leadership and begin setting out what comes next for voters.  “If Trump's a victim of anything, it’s his own success,” Mr Spicer told Sky News host Andrew Bolt.  “He talked about the borders, he solved the borders, he talked about improving the economy, and I think there’s a desire for the American people to say what’s next, what’s next?  “Our party need to stop relying entirely on him.”

title: ‘Feel-good politics’ costs lives: Sean Spicer blasts border failures
description: Former White House press secretary Sean Spicer calls out politicians for focusing on “feel-good” politics rather than citizens' safety.  “These guys all want to be politically correct,” Mr Spicer told Sky News host Andrew Bolt.  “At the end of the day, when someone’s life is lost because they let someone into the country under the guise of feel-good politics.  “We’re living with the consequences and hopefully sending a signal to everyone else that this is not a smart idea.”

title: Disney loses $175 million on ‘leftie’ Snow White flop
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi mocks "uniquely unlikeable" actress Rachel Zegler after a Forbes report estimates Disney’s live-action Snow White lost about $175 million.  “Has Disney finally learnt its lesson, or are we going to keep seeing these leftie projects?” Ms Panahi said.  “She is kind of uniquely unlikable. I think they're punishing her for not listening. Disney told her to pull her head in, and she didn’t.”

title: Meghan’s $250K diamond sparks royal backlash over claims she was never ‘happy’ with Diana ring
description: ‘Kinsey Schofield Unfiltered’ host Kinsey Schofield criticises a “very hard to please” Meghan Markle after she’s been spotted wearing a $250,000 diamond, amid claims she never liked the engagement ring from Prince Harry.  “Is this woman ever happy and content? She tells us she’s in pursuit of joy. Does that just mean a bigger rock?” Ms Schofield told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “Harry designed that ring himself, using diamonds from Princess Diana’s collection … Meghan has modified it multiple times.  “The Sussex brand leads heavily into Hollywood luxury and what’s trending, rather than tradition.”

title: ‘Stop lying’: Angus Taylor wants the Albanese govt held to account over ISIS brides issue
description: Opposition Leader Angus Taylor says the Albanese government must “stop lying” to Australians over the repatriation of ISIS brides.  “If they're not protecting our way of life, then they need to be held to account, stop hiding things,” Mr Taylor told Sky News host Peta Credlin.  “Are we going to see this government keeping these people out because they do not share our core values?”

title: ‘There’s a danger’: Trump fed up with countries not taking immigration seriously
description: Former White House press secretary Sean Spicer warns that countries failing to tighten border controls risk repeating the consequences of open-border policies that were seen in America.  “I think that there’s a danger that’s posed when you have an open border,” Mr Spicer told Sky News host Andrew Bolt.   “We’re watching other countries not take the cues.  “It’s going to yield the same result.”

title: ‘Now a proper criminal investigation’: Former prince Andrew arrested on his 66th birthday
description: ITV News Royal Editor Chris Ship details the alleged arrest of former prince Andrew.  “Confirmation from one of our police forces, it’s Thames Valley Police, which is the police force which looks after Windsor, they’ve confirmed this morning that they have made an arrest of a man in his 60’s,” Mr Ship told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “Guess whose birthday it is today? Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor is 66 years old today.  “He’s been arrested on suspicion of misconduct in public office.  “We have to be super careful when it comes to an active police investigation, and a man, the King's brother, is under arrest.  “It is now a proper criminal investigation.”

title: ‘How the mighty have fallen’: Former prince Andrew arrested for shocking allegations
description: TalkTV host Mark Dolan analyses former prince Andrews arrest for allegations of sharing classified documents.  “This is the monarchy and King Charles' worst nightmare,” Mr Dolan told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “The alleged crime that is being investigated by cops is that, as a trade envoy, he shared classified documents with the disgraced late paedophile Jeffrey Epstein.  “This is the man that had everything.  “How the mighty have fallen.”

title: Albanese under fire for issuing ISIS brides passports
description: Shadow Home Affairs Minister Jonathon Duniam has lashed the Albanese government for not taking national security “seriously” after it was revealed ISIS brides had been issued Australian passports.

title: Keir Starmer states ‘nobody is above the law’ just hours before former prince Andrews arrest
description: Sky News contributor Sophie Elsworth shocked by the unprecedented arrest of former prince Andrew.  “Just earlier this morning, we had UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer ... said that nobody is above the law,” Ms Elsworth told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “It’s the biggest story in the world right now that a member of the Royal family, eighth in line to the throne, is now under arrest by police forces here in Britain.”

title: Former prince Andrew could face ‘maximum sentence of life in prison’
description: Talk TV host Samara Gill reveals that there has not currently been any statement from the royal family after the arrest of former prince Andrew.   “It was unmarked officers that went into his, almost holding pen that he’s in at the moment,” Ms Gill told Sky News host Caleb Bond.  “They [the police] went in there, and they were seen taking laptops out and they’ve basically taken him.  “If he’s proven guilty, then there’s a maximum sentence of life imprisonment for Andrew.”

title: ‘The law must take its course’: The King releases statement after his younger brother’s arrest
description: His Majesty the King has released a statement following the news that his younger brother, former prince Andrew, has been arrested on suspicion of misconduct in public office.   The King expressed deep concern and stated that “the law must take its course”, vowing full support and cooperation with the investigation.   He refrained from further comment, stating that his family will continue their duty and service.
